Hi All,
We design our forms with different fieldsets for a number of reasons. One feature of this design is that we have different numbers of "columns" in different fieldsets. In the current implementation, the file `templates/admin/includes/fieldset.html` at line 21 uses;
```
{% for field in line %}
    <div class="col-md-{{ group_column_width }} form-group ... ">
        {% if field.is_checkbox %}
```
where `group_column_width` is the column width determined from the form as a whole, so if we have some fieldsets with 1 column and some with 4 columns the form will be rendered with all widths as `col-md-3`. This is not my preferred approach but rather;
```
{% for field in line %}
    <div class="col-md-{{ fieldset|fieldset_column_width }} form-group ... ">
        {% if field.is_checkbox %}
```
whereby it determines the right width on a per fieldset basis. Now I can happily patch this at my end, but perhaps the default behavior at the moment is not the preferred implementation for most. I am no expert in django template tags so I can't easily see the way to make the change an option in some way (could one use dummy fields in the fieldset to pad out the absent columns and force alignment???).

Any view on changing the default behaviour to "my way" :-)

